summary: I re-watched some 10th Doctor Christmas specials today, and I concluded that Tennant's exit as the Doctor is in fact, the...
body:
I re-watched some 10th Doctor Christmas specials today, and I concluded that Tennant’s exit as the Doctor is in fact, the saddest. Because not only were we forced to say goodbye to a Doctor that we loved, but we also had to say goodbye to every companion and acquaintance and little piece of backstory that we’d had since the beginning of the reboot. The montage at the end of “The End of Time” wasn’t just 10 saying goodbye to his friends, but it was for the audience to see those characters one last time.

And watching that now, so many years later, it makes me even more sad than I was when I first saw it because I mourn all of those characters and the connections that were forgotten as the new era of new Who took over. I still hold out hope that someday that past will be acknowledged again.

summary:
So it's 3am, I just watched the Catherine Tate/David Tennant Much Ado About Nothing on youtube, and I have thoughts™:
The...
body:
So it’s 3am, I just watched the Catherine Tate/David Tennant Much Ado About Nothing on youtube, and I have thoughts™:

  • The 80s/90s Brits abroad aethestic gives me LIFE.
  • I need Catherine Tate’s dungarees,,,, like yesterday
  • Beatrice and Benedick are such awkward beans and I love them???
  • The drama is so beautifully acted that I nearly cried.
  • The chemistry between Beatrice and Benedick was practically effervescent
  • THEY PLAYED IT AS THE ROM-COM WITH ADDED SOCIAL COMMENTARY THAT IT WAS ALWAYS INTENDED TO BE.
  • I genuinely can’t emphasise enough how funny it is.
  • David Tennant has a magnificent “I’m-not-fucking-around-you-die-tonight” stare. I am scared but also aroused.

I just absolutely adored this production, go watch it on youtube before someone nabs it for copyright.
